    {
      "id": "601-md-intro",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "# Data Science with Java — Venus Notebooks 601\n\nFull showcase of every built-in data science library. **No package installs needed.**\n\n| Library | Auto-imported |\n|---|---|\n| **XChart 3.8** | `XYChart`, `CategoryChart`, `PieChart`, `XYSeries`, `PieStyler`, `SeriesMarkers` |\n| **Commons Math 3** | `DescriptiveStatistics`, `SimpleRegression`, `NormalDistribution`, `TDistribution`, `PearsonsCorrelation`, `SpearmansCorrelation` |\n| **Tablesaw 0.43** | `Table`, `DoubleColumn`, `StringColumn`, `IntColumn`, `BooleanColumn` |\n| **OpenCSV 5** | `CSVReader`, `CSVWriter` |\n| **VenusDisplay** | `show()`, `loadCsv()`, `info()`, `describe()`, `stats()`, `table()` |\n\n> Run all cells with the **Run All** button, or **Shift+Enter** per cell.",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": null,
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": []
    },
    {
      "id": "601-md-s1",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "---\n## Part 1 — Descriptive Statistics\n`DescriptiveStatistics` — mean, median, variance, percentiles, skewness, kurtosis.",
      "output": "",
