    {
      "id": "601-df-build",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "anchor": "df-build",
      "source": "//@ anchor: df-build\n//@ description: Prints Alice\nStringColumn empName = StringColumn.create(\"Name\",\n    new String[]{\"Alice\",\"Bob\",\"Carol\",\"Dave\",\"Eve\",\"Frank\",\"Grace\",\"Hank\"});\nStringColumn empDept = StringColumn.create(\"Dept\",\n    new String[]{\"Eng\",\"Eng\",\"Sales\",\"Sales\",\"Eng\",\"HR\",\"Sales\",\"Eng\"});\nDoubleColumn empSal  = DoubleColumn.create(\"Salary\",\n    new double[]{95000,88000,72000,76000,102000,65000,80000,91000});\nIntColumn empYrs     = IntColumn.create(\"Years\",new int[]{5,3,8,4,7,2,6,4});\nBooleanColumn empSen = BooleanColumn.create(\"Senior\",\n    new boolean[]{true,false,true,false,true,false,false,true});\nTable emp = Table.create(\"Employees\",empName,empDept,empSal,empYrs,empSen);\nSystem.out.println(\"Shape: \"+emp.rowCount()+\" × \"+emp.columnCount());\nVenusDisplay.show(emp);\nVenusDisplay.info(emp);",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": [],
      "description": "Prints Alice"
    },
    {
      "id": "601-df-filter",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "anchor": "df-filter",
      "source": "//@ anchor: df-filter\n//@ depends: df-build\n//@ description: Prints Senior\nTable seniors=emp.where(\n    emp.stringColumn(\"Dept\").isEqualTo(\"Eng\")\n       .and(emp.booleanColumn(\"Senior\").isTrue()));\nSystem.out.println(\"Senior engineers:\"); VenusDisplay.show(seniors);\n\nTable top3=emp.select(\"Name\",\"Dept\",\"Salary\").sortDescendingOn(\"Salary\").first(3);\nSystem.out.println(\"\\nTop 3 earners:\"); VenusDisplay.show(top3);",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "dependsOn": [
        "df-build"
      ],
      "pipelineSteps": [],
      "description": "Prints Senior"
    },
    {
      "id": "601-df-groupby",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "anchor": "df-groupby",
      "source": "//@ anchor: df-groupby\n//@ depends: df-build\n//@ description: Prints Salary\nimport tech.tablesaw.aggregate.AggregateFunctions;\nTable byDept=emp.summarize(\"Salary\",\n    AggregateFunctions.mean,AggregateFunctions.max,AggregateFunctions.count).by(\"Dept\");\nSystem.out.println(\"By department:\"); VenusDisplay.show(byDept);\n\nList<String> depts2=new ArrayList<>(); List<Number> avgs=new ArrayList<>();\nfor(int r=0;r<byDept.rowCount();r++){\n    depts2.add(byDept.stringColumn(0).get(r));\n    avgs.add(byDept.doubleColumn(1).get(r));\n}\nCategoryChart cb=VenusDisplay.barChart(\"Avg Salary by Dept\",\"Dept\",\"Salary ($)\",600,320);\ncb.addSeries(\"Mean\",depts2,avgs); VenusDisplay.show(cb);",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "dependsOn": [
        "df-build"
      ],
      "pipelineSteps": [],
      "description": "Prints Salary"
    },
    {
      "id": "601-df-derive",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "anchor": "df-derive",
      "source": "//@ anchor: df-derive\n//@ depends: df-build\n//@ description: Derive column: salary per year of experience\n// Derive column: salary per year of experience\nDoubleColumn salPerYr=DoubleColumn.create(\"Sal/Year\");\nfor(int r=0;r<emp.rowCount();r++)\n    salPerYr.append(emp.doubleColumn(\"Salary\").get(r)/emp.intColumn(\"Years\").get(r));\nTable enriched=emp.copy(); enriched.addColumns(salPerYr);\nSystem.out.println(\"With Sal/Year:\"); VenusDisplay.show(enriched);\nVenusDisplay.describe(enriched);",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "dependsOn": [
        "df-build"
      ],
      "pipelineSteps": [],
      "description": "Derive column: salary per year of experience"
    },
    {
      "id": "601-md-s7",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "## Part 7 — CSV Loading (OpenCSV + Tablesaw)\nParse CSV with raw OpenCSV reader, then reload the same data via `VenusDisplay.loadCsv()`.",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": null,
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": []
    },
    {
      "id": "601-csv",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "anchor": "load-csv-opencsv",
      "source": "//@ anchor: load-csv-opencsv\n//@ description: Loads and parses CSV data using OpenCSV\nimport com.opencsv.CSVReader;\nimport java.io.StringReader;\nString csvData=\"product,category,price,units\\n\"+\n    \"Widget A,Electronics,29.99,150\\nWidget B,Clothing,49.99,80\\n\"+\n    \"Widget C,Electronics,19.99,320\\nWidget D,Food,5.99,500\\nWidget E,Clothing,89.99,40\";\n\n// Raw OpenCSV\nList<String[]> rawRows=new ArrayList<>();\ntry(CSVReader rdr=new CSVReader(new StringReader(csvData))){ rawRows=rdr.readAll(); }catch(Exception e){}\nSystem.out.printf(\"OpenCSV parsed %d data rows%n\",rawRows.size()-1);\nfor(int i=1;i<rawRows.size();i++){\n    String[] row=rawRows.get(i);\n    System.out.printf(\"  %-10s %-12s $%-6s qty=%s%n\",row[0],row[1],row[2],row[3]);\n}\n\n// Same data via Tablesaw\njava.nio.file.Path tmp=java.nio.file.Files.createTempFile(\"venus-\",\".csv\");\njava.nio.file.Files.writeString(tmp,csvData);\nTable products=VenusDisplay.loadCsv(tmp.toString());\njava.nio.file.Files.delete(tmp);\nVenusDisplay.show(products);\nVenusDisplay.info(products);",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": [],
      "description": "Loads and parses CSV data using OpenCSV"
    },
    {
      "id": "601-md-s8",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "## Part 8 — Multi-Series Time Series\nSimulated 90-day stock prices using random walk + overlay three assets.",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": null,
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": []
    },
    {
      "id": "601-timeseries",
      "type": "CODE",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "anchor": "timeseries",
      "source": "//@ anchor: timeseries\n//@ description: Declares days variable\nRandom rr=new Random(7); int days=90;\ndouble[] t=new double[days],sA=new double[days],sB=new double[days],sC=new double[days];\nsA[0]=sB[0]=sC[0]=100;\nfor(int i=1;i<days;i++){\n    t[i]=i;\n    sA[i]=sA[i-1]*(1+rr.nextGaussian()*0.015+0.0005);\n    sB[i]=sB[i-1]*(1+rr.nextGaussian()*0.010+0.0003);\n    sC[i]=sC[i-1]*(1+rr.nextGaussian()*0.022-0.0002);\n}\nXYChart ts=VenusDisplay.xyChart(\"Simulated 90-Day Stock Prices\",\"Day\",\"Price ($)\",740,400);\nts.getStyler().setMarkerSize(0);\nts.addSeries(\"Stock A\",t,sA); ts.addSeries(\"Stock B\",t,sB); ts.addSeries(\"Stock C\",t,sC);\nVenusDisplay.show(ts);\n\n// Volatility (std dev of daily returns)\nDescriptiveStatistics volA=new DescriptiveStatistics();\nfor(int i=1;i<days;i++) volA.addValue((sA[i]-sA[i-1])/sA[i-1]);\nSystem.out.printf(\"Stock A daily volatility: %.4f (%.2f%%)%n\",\n    volA.getStandardDeviation(), volA.getStandardDeviation()*100);",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": [],
      "description": "Declares days variable"
    },
    {
      "id": "601-md-summary",
      "type": "MARKDOWN",
      "mode": "jshell",
      "source": "## API Quick Reference\n\n### VenusDisplay\n| Call | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `xyChart(t,x,y)` · `barChart(t,x,y)` · `pieChart(t)` | Create chart |\n| `show(chart/table/img)` | Render inline |\n| `loadCsv(path)` | CSV → `Table` |\n| `info(table)` | Column types + missing counts |\n| `describe(table)` | Per-column numeric stats |\n| `stats(label, double[])` | Quick stats HTML table |\n| `table(String[][], hdrs)` | Arbitrary HTML table |\n\n### Tablesaw Table\n| Call | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `Table.create(name, cols...)` | In-memory DataFrame |\n| `table.where(filter)` | Filter rows |\n| `table.select(cols...)` | Column projection |\n| `table.sortDescendingOn(col)` | Sort |\n| `table.first(n)` / `table.last(n)` | Head / tail |\n| `table.summarize(col, fns).by(col)` | GroupBy aggregate |\n| `table.copy().addColumns(col)` | Derived column |\n\n### Commons Math\n| Class | Key methods |\n|---|---|\n| `DescriptiveStatistics` | `getMean()` `getPercentile(p)` `getStandardDeviation()` `getSkewness()` |\n| `SimpleRegression` | `addData(x,y)` `getSlope()` `getRSquare()` `predict(x)` |\n| `NormalDistribution(μ,σ)` | `density(x)` `cumulativeProbability(x)` `inverseCumulativeProbability(p)` |\n| `PearsonsCorrelation` | `correlation(x[],y[])` |\n| `SpearmansCorrelation` | `correlation(x[],y[])` |",
      "output": "",
      "returnValue": null,
      "executed": false,
      "executionCount": null,
      "error": "",
      "anchor": null,
      "dependsOn": [],
      "pipelineSteps": []
    }
  ],
